00:58:17,971 --> 00:58:21,352
And it's about time, if we're interested in

720
00:58:22,019 --> 00:58:25,662
Revitalizing, Councilor Caviello is interested in Salem Street.

721
00:58:25,682 --> 00:58:27,163
He brings up the Haines Square area.

722
00:58:27,583 --> 00:58:29,425
But we have to look at the hillside.

723
00:58:29,445 --> 00:58:32,827
We have to look at South Meffitt, West Meffitt, Meffitt Square.

724
00:58:33,068 --> 00:58:36,630
We have to look at every particular area, Mr. President, in the square.

725
00:58:37,071 --> 00:58:38,652
And we have to have a game plan.

726
00:58:39,392 --> 00:58:47,278
There is no, when we were talking about capital improvements a few years back, the one thing that was lacking was there was no vision.

727
00:58:47,679 --> 00:58:50,761
There was never a capital improvement plan established in this community.

728
00:58:51,943 --> 00:58:54,465
And we're seeing the same with our business districts.

729
00:58:54,925 --> 00:58:57,947
There is no plan to revitalize our squares.

730
00:58:58,708 --> 00:59:08,193
And, you know, we can refer back to the mayor's three proposals for revitalizing Method Square, but none of them have made it out of infancy.

731
00:59:08,574 --> 00:59:13,236
They're all still in the baby carriage, and they never make it any further than that.

732
00:59:13,817 --> 00:59:17,859
And every so often, people get upset and say, what's going on in our squares?

733
00:59:17,919 --> 00:59:19,000
I see all these vacancies.

734
00:59:19,720 --> 00:59:21,561
After 7 o'clock, the square's dead.

735
00:59:21,581 --> 00:59:37,028
And all you need to do is look around other communities and see what Wakefield's doing, see what Redding's doing, see what Stoneham's doing, see what downtown Woburn's doing in areas that before, you know, really weren't, you know, bustling.

736
00:59:37,408 --> 00:59:38,249
Now we're bustling.

737
00:59:38,689 --> 00:59:45,412
And here we are five minutes from Boston off of Major 93, and our square is dead, Mr. President.

738
00:59:46,153 --> 00:59:47,073
It really is a shame.

739
00:59:47,937 --> 00:59:52,219
And I know there's a group of residents that have organized around this issue.

740
00:59:52,879 --> 00:59:56,460
I'm hoping they step forward and bring this to light.

741
00:59:56,520 --> 01:00:07,784
But I don't think we can afford to sit around any longer and discuss a possible Peace Garden or a water taxi as the solve-all for Method Square.

742
01:00:08,105 --> 01:00:12,326
You know, once we bring in a water taxi, all of a sudden the square is going to be bustling.

743
01:00:12,806 --> 01:00:17,168
Or once the Peace Garden comes in, it's going to attract people into the square.

744
01:00:17,714 --> 01:00:19,116
I don't think that's going to be the case.

745
01:00:19,216 --> 01:00:20,879
This is not the field of dreams.

746
01:00:20,939 --> 01:00:21,920
If you build it, they'll come.

747
01:00:22,621 --> 01:00:27,067
In my opinion, the city's going to have to step forward, do some legwork in the issue.

748
01:00:27,484 --> 01:00:28,524
It's not going to just happen.

749
01:00:28,845 --> 01:00:33,166
We have three large parcels of land in our downtown business district.

750
01:00:33,586 --> 01:00:36,808
Any other community would die to have that, Mr. President.

751
01:00:37,128 --> 01:00:38,148
We own the property.

752
01:00:38,188 --> 01:00:39,789
We don't have to go in by eminent domain.

753
01:00:40,069 --> 01:00:41,249
We don't have to do anything.

754
01:00:41,490 --> 01:00:42,470
That's our property.

755
01:00:42,790 --> 01:00:44,991
We can revitalize that on our own.

756
01:00:45,551 --> 01:00:49,573
And these parcels have been sitting there vacant for years and years and years.

757
01:00:50,453 --> 01:00:52,614
I just don't know what it's going to take, Mr. President.

758
01:00:52,994 --> 01:00:54,875
