01:06:32,985 --> 01:06:37,488
I mean, his whole family around him, the man saw all his friends.

833
01:06:37,968 --> 01:06:45,472
He knew people were very, very morose because a loving family member and a good friend was dying.

834
01:06:46,052 --> 01:06:54,397
Cardinal Sean informed him that his Holy Father, the Pope in Rome, had elevated Father Mime to Monsignor.

835
01:06:55,497 --> 01:06:58,399
And this is a true testament to his character, his response

836
01:06:58,943 --> 01:07:01,525
was, well, it's about time.

837
01:07:02,426 --> 01:07:11,733
And they all, I mean, here's a man who immediately relieves the morosity of the situation for his family and friends.

838
01:07:12,274 --> 01:07:15,957
And it was just such a wonderful homily today by Father Toomey of St.

839
01:07:16,037 --> 01:07:16,597
Raphael's.

840
01:07:16,757 --> 01:07:23,823
And if I could, I could please, I mean, a lot of folks in Medford would love probably to have just a brief moment of silence.

841
01:07:23,863 --> 01:07:26,005
And thank you so much, Councilor Camuso.

842
01:07:31,148 --> 01:07:31,828
Thank you.

843
01:07:31,968 --> 01:07:40,652
And if I could, from the chair, say that Monsignor Meem was a wonderful, among all his other qualities, he was an outstanding preacher.

844
01:07:41,173 --> 01:07:42,613
He knew how to preach the word of God.

845
01:07:43,014 --> 01:07:46,075
We have two other condolences that we're going to mention.

846
01:07:46,115 --> 01:07:58,261
If I could just add to really quick that our own city solicitor, Mark Rumley, who's the deacon of our parish too, was also very comforting and inhaling at a time of serious grief.

847
01:07:58,321 --> 01:08:00,662
And I want to thank him for his

848
01:08:02,212 --> 01:08:07,855
outstanding leader as a spiritual leader in my parish and church.

849
01:08:07,915 --> 01:08:08,295
Thank you.

850
01:08:08,715 --> 01:08:10,036
Thank you, Mr. Capucci.

851
01:08:10,436 --> 01:08:31,066
We also have two condolences in addition to this, two offered for the same person, one by Councilor Caravaglio 15-037, be it resolved that the council offers sincere condolences to the family of Medford High School Red Sox and Yankee pitcher,

852
01:08:31,527 --> 01:09:00,708
Bill Monboquette on his recent passing, and also offered by Councilor Penta, 15-038, be it resolved that an expression of sympathy be extended to the family of Medford baseball great Bill Monboquette on his recent passing, and that all Medford sports teams and their players recognize the wonderful accomplishment that he accomplished at a time when playing for a professional major league baseball team and achieving his baseball statistics certainly made Medford proud.

853
01:09:01,842 --> 01:09:03,604
Do we want either of you to speak on this?

854
01:09:05,245 --> 01:09:06,145
Yes, Councilor Penta.

855
01:09:08,887 --> 01:09:19,455
The recent passing of Bill Mumbo-Katt here in the city of Medford, I think really highlights the fact that he is somewhat of a baseball legend, probably.

856
01:09:19,935 --> 01:09:30,483
Medford has been blessed with many, many baseball players, but this gentleman did it at a time back in the early 50s when he was practicing with a fellow by the name of Gus Hennessey.

857
01:09:31,312 --> 01:09:33,773
And they would go down and play Stead Park continuously.

858
01:09:33,933 --> 01:09:36,133
And he would just pitch to them and pitch to them and pitch to them.

859
01:09:36,953 --> 01:09:39,194
And eventually, he finally made it.

860
01:09:39,454 --> 01:09:41,194
But he made it in a time and a period.

861
01:09:42,014 --> 01:09:43,074
Eddie Finn, you remember this.

862
01:09:43,414 --> 01:09:46,555
He made it in a time that there was only eight professional baseball teams in either seat.

863
01:09:47,075 --> 01:09:47,855
Now there's 32.

864
01:09:47,895 --> 01:09:51,736
But there was only eight American League teams, eight National League teams.

865
01:09:52,316 --> 01:09:52,876
And it was tough.

866
01:09:52,996 --> 01:09:55,737
And when he went into the minors, he just didn't come up right away.

867
01:09:55,757 --> 01:09:57,297
He had to earn his spot.

868
01:09:57,577 --> 01:10:00,938
And he has a very interesting baseball career.

869
01:10:01,450 --> 01:10:09,633
But one of his real major accomplishments, and I don't even think he realized it until it happened, they were playing against the Washington Senators on a particular night.

870
01:10:09,673 --> 01:10:13,455
And I believe he had struck out 17 baseball, 17 players.

871
01:10:14,875 --> 01:10:21,838
And the coach of the Washington Senators, his name was William McCauley, came up to him toward the end of the game.

872
01:10:22,158 --> 01:10:23,639
And somebody wants to talk to him.

873
01:10:23,659 --> 01:10:24,659
The president wants to talk to him.

874
01:10:24,679 --> 01:10:25,439
That's the terminology.

875
01:10:25,719 --> 01:10:26,760
The president wants to talk to him.

876
01:10:26,780 --> 01:10:30,041
And he thought it was the president of the baseball team or the president of the league and this and that.

877
01:10:30,425 --> 01:10:31,565
But it was Dwight Eisenhower.

878
01:10:32,826 --> 01:10:37,507
And Dwight Eisenhower was so impressed with him that he wanted a ball signed by him.

879
01:10:37,527 --> 01:10:40,228
And when the president asked him, where did you come from?

880
01:10:40,288 --> 01:10:41,068
And he says, Meffa.

881
01:10:41,908 --> 01:10:42,228
Meffa.

882
01:10:42,728 --> 01:10:46,510
And it was sort of like, and he says, why do all you people down there talk like that?

883
01:10:46,530 --> 01:10:47,710
I mean, what do you?

884
01:10:47,970 --> 01:10:50,531
And it was kind of like, it was a cool situation.

885
01:10:50,911 --> 01:10:58,773
But the night he threw his no-hitter in Chicago on August 1, 1962 against a veteran, a very good veteran pitcher, early win.

886
01:10:59,741 --> 01:11:02,283
That was a real highlight here in the city of Medford.

887
01:11:02,863 --> 01:11:06,565
No one had ever thrown a, no one ever came from Medford to throw it.

888
01:11:07,225 --> 01:11:22,654
And if I have my story correctly, I believe when he came back to Medford at that time, engine six drove him, picked him up and gave him somewhat of a mini parade here in the city of Medford, acknowledging the fact that who he was and how he was, you know, he was an all-star pitcher for the all-star teams for years.

889
01:11:22,714 --> 01:11:27,416
He played professional, he pitched professional baseball for 11 years between the Red Sox and the Yankees.

890
01:11:29,385 --> 01:11:42,434
And I guess his ending comment, which I happened to notice, and I'm glad that they printed it in the local press, he made the comment that he loved playing baseball so much that he would have played for nothing.

891
01:11:43,374 --> 01:11:50,859
And if people only would realize what that would mean to today's kids that are playing professional sports, okay?

892
01:11:50,879 --> 01:11:52,440
They're into the millions and millions of dollars.

893
01:11:52,480 --> 01:11:58,004
I believe when he was pitching, the year he threw the no-hitter, he was making $8,000, and I believe they offered him up to 12.

894
01:11:59,126 --> 01:12:00,066
the following year.

895
01:12:00,086 --> 01:12:03,928
And that's just craziness for money back then.

896
01:12:04,548 --> 01:12:10,391
And if you look at him today, what his statistics would have been and what he could have probably earned, it's probably just unfathomable.

897
01:12:10,771 --> 01:12:12,612
But it's baseball as it was then.

898
01:12:13,032 --> 01:12:13,812
That's what they paid.

899
01:12:13,872 --> 01:12:14,793
That's what it was all about.

900
01:12:15,473 --> 01:12:22,176
But I think it would be a great opportunity for the Medford sports kids to know that this fellow grew up here in the city of Medford.

901
01:12:22,576 --> 01:12:24,157
He worked this thing into the ground.

902
01:12:24,957 --> 01:12:26,078
He played it.

903
01:12:26,178 --> 01:12:26,738
He loved it.

904
01:12:27,253 --> 01:12:29,194
He used to come back and watch Meffitt High Baseball.

905
01:12:29,214 --> 01:12:34,377
He used to come back because of family members at Meffitt High School Hockey.

906
01:12:35,058 --> 01:12:38,540
He just really was a true gentleman to the sport.

907
01:12:38,580 --> 01:12:41,181
He wasn't flamboyant or anything like that.

908
01:12:41,221 --> 01:12:49,246
He was just a regular guy who just proved here in the city of Meffitt and any place else in this country, if you work hard enough at something that you want, it'd be great by today's standards.

909
01:12:49,286 --> 01:12:53,108
I mean, like I said, I had a whole list of 32 names of people who

910
01:12:53,850 --> 01:12:56,311
made professional sports through the minor leagues.

911
01:12:56,331 --> 01:12:57,832
But this guy made it in the majors.

912
01:12:58,332 --> 01:13:01,154
And he made it in such a way that nobody expected to happen.

913
01:13:01,234 --> 01:13:10,519
And he just made the city of Medford so proud to know that, you know, he could accomplish what he did for the city of Medford, for professional baseball, because he loved it.

914
01:13:10,559 --> 01:13:12,400
And like he said, he would have done it for nothing.

915
01:13:12,540 --> 01:13:13,200
And you know something?

916
01:13:13,460 --> 01:13:16,782
He probably did play for nothing, because that's how much he really loved the sport.

917
01:13:17,302 --> 01:13:22,405
And to his wife, Josephine, and the family, you know, you can be very proud of the fact that you had a great husband.

918
01:13:22,972 --> 01:13:26,133
who did the city of Medford proud, and you did him proud as well.

919
01:13:26,293 --> 01:13:29,153
So with that being said, Mr. President, I'd like to pass that on.

920
01:13:29,173 --> 01:13:30,153
Thank you, Mr. Councilor.

921
01:13:30,173 --> 01:13:30,533
Councilor Knight?

922
01:13:31,734 --> 01:13:32,474
Yes, Mr. President.

923
01:13:32,494 --> 01:13:36,094
I'd like to thank both Councilors Caviello and Penta for bringing this resolution forward.

924
01:13:36,575 --> 01:13:47,076
I think it's important to point out for those of us at home who would like to maybe understand Mr. Mombo-Kett's story a little bit better, that it is memorialized down at Placed at Park, right behind home plate.

925
01:13:47,116 --> 01:13:50,097
There is a plaque down there that speaks about his achievements and

926
01:13:51,065 --> 01:13:59,652
his professional achievements, but also his personal achievements and what he's done in the community of Medford to improve our quality of life here and to improve the lives of young athletes in the city, Mr. President.

927
01:13:59,893 --> 01:14:00,813
Thank you, Councilor Knight.

928
01:14:00,853 --> 01:14:01,694
Councilor Caravaglio.

929
01:14:04,476 --> 01:14:05,397
Thank you, Mr. President.

930
01:14:06,238 --> 01:14:08,700
My dad was a good friend of Bill Maumbo-Katt.

931
01:14:08,740 --> 01:14:09,821
They grew up in the same neighborhood.

932
01:14:10,962 --> 01:14:18,548
In fact, I know this sounds corny, but the first baseball game I went to, my dad took me with tickets that Bill Maumbo-Katt had given him.

933
01:14:19,235 --> 01:14:22,356
And I got to go down on the field and meet him, you know, caught him on a graph ball.

934
01:14:23,356 --> 01:14:26,177
And, you know, I just wanted to say, you know, he was a good guy.

935
01:14:26,217 --> 01:14:28,998
I'd see him all the time down at Dickey's gas station, getting gas all the time.

936
01:14:29,539 --> 01:14:30,679
Always asked my dad all the time.

937
01:14:30,739 --> 01:14:32,600
And I'd like to wish the family well.

938
01:14:33,240 --> 01:14:34,520
Thank you.

939
01:14:36,201 --> 01:14:37,221
Thank you, Mr. President.

940
01:14:37,241 --> 01:14:42,063
I remember when they had the dedication down at Placed at Park some many years ago.

941
01:14:42,803 --> 01:14:44,944
That was the first time I met Bill Mumbo-Katt.

942
01:14:45,660 --> 01:14:59,270
And out of all the accolades, as Councilor Penter alluded to, no hitter and all-star league named and so forth, the one thing that stands out to me was his commitment to local youth.

943
01:15:00,110 --> 01:15:07,956
And he never looked for any fanfare, never looked for any recognition, but he'd always be at certain events, Mr. President.

944
01:15:08,736 --> 01:15:09,977
And, you know,

945
01:15:10,353 --> 01:15:33,524
And I think it meant a lot, even though the younger kids, you know, you hear the name and you could tell them who he was, you know, really could never appreciate that this man was, in his time, was someone that was really looked up to and someone that was at the top of his game, at the top of his sport, never had anything negative mentioned about him.

946
01:15:34,284 --> 01:15:40,167
In today's day and age, when you hear about sports players, there's always something mentioned after the name.

947
01:15:40,630 --> 01:15:42,391
And with Bill Mumbo, you never got that.

948
01:15:42,852 --> 01:15:54,039
As Councilor Penta mentioned and the other councilors, he was a stand-up gentleman, a family man, and again, gave so much back to a community that he loved so much.

949
01:15:54,760 --> 01:15:59,263
And I'll always remember him for being part of the local youth in this community.

950
01:15:59,663 --> 01:16:00,644
Thank you, Councilor Marks.

951
01:16:03,305 --> 01:16:10,170
Next, offered by Councilor Penta, be it resolved that an expression of sympathy be extended to the family and friends of Stephen Brown,

